Consider the binarized version of the travel review dataset shown in Table 4. The matrix can be considered as representing N = 10 transactions o1, o2, ..., o10 and M = 9 items f1, f2, ..., f9. Which of the following options represents all (non-empty) itemsets with support greater than 0.15 (and only itemsets with support greater than 0.15)?

A. {f1}, {f2}, {f3}, {f4}, {f5}, {f2,f3}, {f2,f5}, {f3,f4}, {f3,f5}, {f4,f5}, {f2,f3,f5}, {f3,f4,f5}
B. {f3}, {f4}, {f5}, {f3,f4}, {f3,f5}
C. {f3}, {f4}, {f5}, {f3,f4}, {f3,f5}, {f4,f5}, {f3,f4,f5}
D. {f1}, {f2}, {f3}, {f4}, {f5}
